(A) Variation of fluorescence response of probe (BSA-CuNCs quenched with Fe3+) towards bilirubin in urine samples at different dilutions (10X, 100X & 1000X; 
   λ

ex = 320 nm, [Fe3+] = 66 μM, pH = 11.4); (b) Variation of fluorescence response of the probe (BSA-CuNCs quenched with Fe3+) towards urea, creatine and glucose in urine samples at different dilutions (10X, 100X and 1000 X; 
   λ

ex = 320 nm, [Fe3+] = 66 μM, [urea] = 0.01548 M, [creatine] = 0.5109 mM, [glucose] = 0.9158 mM); (c) Fluorescence response of the probe (BSA-CuNCs quenched with Fe3+) showing the cumulative influence of biomolecules by adding 20 μL of urea, creatine and glucose followed by addition of bilirubin. ([Fe3+] = 66 μM, [urea] = 0.0154 M, [creatine] = 0.5109 mM, [glucose] = 0.9158 mM, [Bilirubin] = 0.2–1.2 μM, pH = 11.4, λex = 320 nm); (d) Variation in fluorescence response of bilirubin in serum samples at different dilutions (10X, 100X & 1000X; [BRadults] = 170 μM, [BRnewborns] = 340 μM, pH = 11.4).
